---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AffiliateCTA from '../../components/AffiliateCTA.astro';
import Card from '../../components/Card.astro';
import { AFFILIATE_LINKS as affiliates } from '../../config/affiliate-links';

const title = 'AI Website Builders with Code Export (2025)';
const description = 'Which AI website builders let you export code? Framer (React), Dorik (HTML), and others. Complete comparison.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-orange-600 font-semibold mb-4">CATEGORY</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">AI Website Builders with Code Export</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-6">
        Want to build with AI then host elsewhere? These builders let you export code.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-orange-50 border-l-4 border-orange-500 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Quick Ranking</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2">
        <li><strong>Framer:</strong> React code export (developer-friendly)</li>
        <li><strong>Dorik:</strong> HTML/CSS/JS export (easiest for non-developers)</li>
        <li><strong>TeleportHQ:</strong> Multiple export formats</li>
        <li><strong>Webflow:</strong> HTML/CSS/JS export (on paid plans)</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4">
        <strong>Important:</strong> Wix, Squarespace, Durable, and 10Web do NOT allow code export. You are locked into their hosting.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-12">
      <Card title="Framer - React Export" subtitle="Best for Developers">
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          Framer exports clean React code that developers can work with. Perfect if you know React or want to learn.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <strong>Pros:</strong> Modern React, component-based, growing ecosystem
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Cons:</strong> Requires React knowledge, not for beginners
        </p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="Dorik - HTML Export" subtitle="Best for Non-Developers">
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          Dorik exports standard HTML/CSS/JS that anyone can host anywhere. No frameworks required.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <strong>Pros:</strong> Simple, works anywhere, no dependencies
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Cons:</strong> Less modern than React, harder to customize
        </p>
      </Card>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Why Code Export Matters</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Avoid Vendor Lock-In</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            With code export, you can leave the builder anytime. Your site is yours. Without it, you are stuck paying forever or starting over.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Host Anywhere</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Exported code can be hosted on Netlify, Vercel, AWS, GitHub Pages, or any web host. More control, potentially lower costs.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Full Customization</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Exported code can be modified arbitrarily. Want a feature the builder does not support? Add it yourself.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">The Tradeoff</h2>

      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-500 p-6 mb-8">
        <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
          <strong>Reality:</strong> Code export sounds great but requires technical skills. Most people are better off staying with builder hosting.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <strong>Choose code export if:</strong>
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 ml-4 mb-4">
        <li>You are a developer or comfortable with code</li>
        <li>You need custom features builders do not offer</li>
        <li>You want to host on your own infrastructure</li>
        <li>You are concerned about vendor lock-in</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-gray-700">
        <strong>Stick with builder hosting if:</strong>
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 ml-4">
        <li>You are not technical</li>
        <li>You want the builder to handle everything</li>
        <li>You do not want to manage hosting</li>
        <li>You prefer convenience over control</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Recommendation</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <strong>For developers:</strong> Choose Framer for React export. Modern, powerful, and the code is actually maintainable.
      </p>

      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <strong>For everyone else:</strong> Do not worry about code export. Builder hosting is fine for 95% of use cases.
      </p>

      <p class="text-gray-700">
        <strong>Truth:</strong> Most people who say they want code export never actually use it. The complexity is not worth it for simple sites.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center space-y-4">
      <AffiliateCTA
        href={affiliates.framer.affiliateUrl}
        commission={affiliates.framer.commission}
        label="Try Framer (React Export)"
        className="bg-orange-600 hover:bg-orange-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold text-lg inline-block"
      />
      <br/>
      <AffiliateCTA
        href={affiliates.dorik.affiliateUrl}
        commission={affiliates.dorik.commission}
        label="Try Dorik (HTML Export)"
        className="bg-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-900 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold text-lg inline-block"
      />
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
